<HL>
   Business Brief -- Chrysler Corp.:
   Canadian Unit Will Spend
   $253.2 Million on Facility
</HL>
<DATE>
05/25/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A2
</SO>
<CO>
   C
</CO>
<IN>
AUTOMOBILES (AUT)
</IN>
<LP>
   Chrysler Canada Ltd., said it plans to spend 300 million
Canadian dollars ($253.2 million) at its Windsor, Ontario,
minivan plant.
   The Toronto-based company said C$21 million will be spent
in plant improvements at the facility, with the remaining
C$280 million to be spent on product development. The plant
will build the redesigned 1991 minivan.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The Canadian unit of Chrysler Corp. also said its Pillette
Road assembly plant in Windsor has "a good future." There had
been some talk of the plant's being shut down. The plant is
Chrysler's only source of large, rear-wheel-drive commercial
vans and wagons.
   Chrylser Canada said it will invest more than C$100
million in new equipment and plant improvements at the
Pillette plant over the next three years.
</TEXT>
